      },
      "lineNbr": 241,
      "author": {
        "id": 1150179
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-28T13:11:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "qq: why it\u0027s not /tmp ?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 241,
        "startChar": 35,
        "endLine": 241,
        "endChar": 50
      },
      "revId": "15f6df002bceb993a7924556721eec7662c73ef8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "32b52059_b8e019cc",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/cmd/tast/run/config.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 241,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-09-02T03:42:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "/tmp is on-memory tmpfs, but /usr/local/tmp is ext4 stateful partition. Writing a lot of files to /tmp can lead to out of disk.",
      "parentUuid": "b9760c6d_5314ccd9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 241,
        "startChar": 35,
        "endLine": 241,
        "endChar": 50
      },
      "revId": "15f6df002bceb993a7924556721eec7662c73ef8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9185755d_7999541c",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/cmd/tast/run/config.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 241,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-09-02T03:42:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Keigo:\n\nRandom seed is a very good point, I overlooked that! I think adding nanosecond part is sufficient to avoid conflicts. Let me choose that approach.\n\n\nHidehiko:\n\nI considered the approach to put OutDir field in RunStart control message (which is sent at the beginning of the runner execution), but I chose this this approach because it simplifies code flow.\n\nAs you may know, one of the things I\u0027ve been trying to remove from Tast framework is logic to decide a value in run.Config in the middle of test execution. With this approach we can move forward to this goal for cfg.localOutDir.\n\nAs for conflicts, I think that\u0027s a matter of probability. I guess you\u0027re fine with this approach if I put 512bit true randomness to the file name generated here (otherwise you can\u0027t trust SHA512). What is the threshold you\u0027ll be satisfied with?",
      "parentUuid": "26f790c3_9850f1d4",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 240,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 241,
        "endChar": 116
      },
      "revId": "15f6df002bceb993a7924556721eec7662c73ef8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f0cb152a_ac7bb499",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/cmd/tast/run/config.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
